dismissalText.commentary: Nazmul Hossain lbw b White 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: all squared up by the googly, White mixes it up well, pitches outside off and cuts back in sharply, catches Nazmul on the back foot, that was fairly plumb in front

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza c Haddin b Johnson 8 (27b 0x4 0x6 43m) SR: 29.62

dismissalComment.html: terrific delivery from Johnson and that would have claimed even the best batsman, angles it into the right hander and lands it back of a length, the ball then moves away from Mortaza after pitching and all he can do is tamely edge it to Haddin

dismissalText.commentary: Shaun Marsh not out 69 (81b 9x4 1x6 113m) SR: 85.18
Shane Watson lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 29 (33b 3x4 0x6 64m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: Bangladesh have something to smile about, Shakib pushes that flatter and faster, lands on middle and leg, Watson commits a little too early to the sweep and the ball hits him in front of middle stump
Bangladesh have something to smile about, Shakib pushes that flatter and faster, lands on middle and leg, Watson commits a little too early to the sweep and the ball hits him in front of middle stump
a few more smiles for the men in green, Clarke suddenly has a rush of blood and  gives him the charge, he's beaten in flight and fails to drag his foot back before Ghosh effects the stumping

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 29 (33b 3x4 0x6 64m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: Bangladesh have something to smile about, Shakib pushes that flatter and faster, lands on middle and leg, Watson commits a little too early to the sweep and the ball hits him in front of middle stump

dismissalText.long: st Dhiman Ghosh b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke st Dhiman Ghosh b Shakib Al Hasan 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: a few more smiles for the men in green, Clarke suddenly has a rush of blood and  gives him the charge, he's beaten in flight and fails to drag his foot back before Ghosh effects the stumping

commentTextItems.html: And Marsh completes the formalities as the short ball is cut through cover

commentPostTextItems.html: Another one-sided encounter and that's the series for Australia. Marsh continues to be among the runs and he picks up the Man-of-the-Match award for his unbeaten 69. Do join us for the final one-dayer on Saturday. Hope Bangladesh put up a better show. On behalf of Kanishkaa Balachandran, this is Siddarth Ravindran signing off

commentTextItems.html: Marsh comes down the track and lofts it back over the bowlers head and that has carried all the way for six

commentPostTextItems.html: One shot away from a series win now

commentTextItems.html: similar delivery, sweep attempted again, gets a top edge and trickles towards fine leg
pitches outside leg, Marsh goes for the big sweep but doesn't connect
soft hands, defended to the off, thinks about a single but decides against it

headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: in the corridor outside off, Hussey shoulders arms
some width offered and he cuts it to point
outside off and he watches it through to the keeper
short of a length, on middle and leg, defended to the off side
tried to smash that down the ground, but mistimes it and doesn't beat the bowler
comes down the ground, wristy shot through square leg

headshotImage.caption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: back of a length, he backed away crashed that through cover. Superb footwork there
worked away behind square on the leg side
defended off the back foot
pitched just outside off and turned in, got the outside edge, falls wide of slip
driven to mid-off for a single
full outside off, he takes a couple of paces forward and swings across the line to bring up his fifty

headshotImage.caption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: pitches outside off and holds its line before reaching Ghosh
he lunges forward and tries to steer this wide of point, his fifty will have to wait
safely shoulders arms outside the off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Alok Kapali c Watson b Hopes 2 (9b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 22.22

dismissalComment.html: very very soft dismissal, Kapali decides to take the aerial route this time but fails to execute it properly as he tamely chips a full delivery down to Watson at mid-off who's standing well forward from the conventional position, Bangladesh just can't get sizable partnerships going

dismissalText.commentary: Abdur Razzak c Clarke b White 9 (26b 1x4 0x6 33m) SR: 34.61

dismissalComment.html: attempts a leg break and Razzak expects it to turn, the ball however goes through straight and Razzak can't get behind the line to defend, the outside edge lobs to Clarke at first slip

dismissalText.commentary: Dhiman Ghosh c Watson b Clark 30 (36b 1x4 1x6 63m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: he goes for broke straight down the ground but makes a mess of it, he stays rooted to the crease as he faces up a full delivery from Clark, the top edge travels to Watson at mid-off who pedals backwards to take the catch, terrible shot and Ghosh will regret it

dismissalText.commentary: Nazmul Hossain lbw b White 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: all squared up by the googly, White mixes it up well, pitches outside off and cuts back in sharply, catches Nazmul on the back foot, that was fairly plumb in front

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza c Haddin b Johnson 8 (27b 0x4 0x6 43m) SR: 29.62

dismissalComment.html: terrific delivery from Johnson and that would have claimed even the best batsman, angles it into the right hander and lands it back of a length, the ball then moves away from Mortaza after pitching and all he can do is tamely edge it to Haddin

dismissalText.commentary: Shaun Marsh not out 69 (81b 9x4 1x6 113m) SR: 85.18
Shane Watson lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 29 (33b 3x4 0x6 64m) SR: 87.87

dismissalComment.html: Bangladesh have something to smile about, Shakib pushes that flatter and faster, lands on middle and leg, Watson commits a little too early to the sweep and the ball hits him in front of middle stump

dismissalText.long: st Dhiman Ghosh b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke st Dhiman Ghosh b Shakib Al Hasan 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: a few more smiles for the men in green, Clarke suddenly has a rush of blood and  gives him the charge, he's beaten in flight and fails to drag his foot back before Ghosh effects the stumping

stories.title: 'It's just not happening for us' - Ashraful
stories.subTitle: Australia v Bangladesh, 2nd ODI, Darwin
stories.summary: It was yet another batting failure for Bangladesh - they were skittled for 117 - and Mohammad Ashraful, the captain, said his side weren't performing to potential

stories.title: Marsh makes his own mark
stories.subTitle: Australia v Bangladesh, 2nd ODI, Darwin
stories.summary: Shaun Marsh's first two one-day internationals at home could hardly have gone any better. Having made a success of his debut ODI series in the West Indies this year, Marsh has continued his excellent form with a pair of half-centuries in Darwin

stories.title: Marsh guides Australia to easy win
stories.subTitle: Australia v Bangladesh, 2nd ODI, Darwin
stories.summary: Bangladesh improved marginally but still lost by eight wickets in Darwin, where Australia's bowlers set up an unassailable 2-0 series lead
stories.byline: The Bulletin by Brydon Coverdale in Darwin

stories.title: Fit Watson keen to open again
stories.subTitle: Australia v Bangladesh, 2nd ODI, Darwin
stories.summary: Two months ago in the Caribbean, Shane Watson brutalised the West Indies attack to register his first one-day international century while suffering from a broken toe. Now back to full fitness, he is looking forward to discovering what he can do to the Ban

stories.summary: Bangladesh hope to expose Australia's lack of match practice in the first ODI in Darwin
